As indicated below, VTK merge request 13053 removed the functionality where
unknown image types were simply ignored during load (with errors being
thrown only if they got used). This restores the branch and logic.

--- IO/Geometry/vtkGLTFDocumentLoader.cxx
+++ IO/Geometry/vtkGLTFDocumentLoader.cxx
@@ -907,8 +908,15 @@ bool vtkGLTFDocumentLoader::LoadImageData()
 
       if (!reader)
       {
-        vtkErrorMacro("No supported reader found for image " << image.Name);
-        return false;
+        // Note: this was the default functionality for unrecognized image
+        // formats prior to Merge request 13053.
+        // It is perfectly valid to declare other extension-supported image types
+        // so long as they are never required by the scene. Therefore, the possible
+        // error is deferred until later.
+        image.ImageData = nullptr;
+        // This patch is messing with the progress event; we won't get progress
+        // updates for every unrecognized image type, but that's ok.
+        continue;
       }
     }
 
